<Skein rootNode="node-1">
  <generator>Windows Inform 10.1.2</generator>
  <item nodeId="node-1">
    <command xml:space="preserve">Before Andromeda</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">============================================================&#x000A;&#x000A;        BEFORE ANDROMEDA: THE SKY BREAKS                    &#x000A;&#x000A;             Episode 1 -- The Sky Breaks                    &#x000A;&#x000A;============================================================&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;You are Zaryn, a young Ghanrion -- a sentient being native to this&#x000A;&#x000A;bioluminescent world, gifted with weak but growing telepathic ability.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your people have lived in peaceful isolation within the forest for as&#x000A;&#x000A;long as memory reaches.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Last night, something fell from the sky.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Now the forest holds its breath.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;============================================================&#x000A;&#x000A;                     HOW TO PLAY                             &#x000A;&#x000A;============================================================&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Movement -- Navigate between locations:&#x000A;&#x000A;   NORTH  /  SOUTH  /  EAST  /  WEST  /  UP  /  DOWN&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Observation -- Learn about your surroundings:&#x000A;&#x000A;   LOOK                    -- describe the current room&#x000A;&#x000A;   EXAMINE &lt;thing&gt;       -- inspect a character or object&#x000A;&#x000A;   MAP  or  LOOK MAP       -- display the world map and all locations&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Characters -- Speak with the people around you:&#x000A;&#x000A;   TALK TO ZARB            -- speak with the young Ghanrion scout&#x000A;&#x000A;   TALK TO XILAR           -- speak with the wounded warrior (Ravine)&#x000A;&#x000A;   TALK TO VAEL            -- speak with the tribal elder (Ghanrion Camp)&#x000A;&#x000A;   TALK TO CAPTAIN JACK    -- speak with the human officer (Crash Site)&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Special Actions -- Interact with the world:&#x000A;&#x000A;   HELP XILAR              -- attempt to free a trapped ally in the Ravine&#x000A;&#x000A;   FREE XILAR              -- same as above&#x000A;&#x000A;   USE TELEPATHY           -- broadcast a weak mental signal through the forest&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Story Choices -- Available during the final sequence:&#x000A;&#x000A;   HELP VAEL               -- stand with the elder&#x000A;&#x000A;   GUIDE YOUNG             -- lead the children to safety&#x000A;&#x000A;   OBSERVE                 -- watch events unfold&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Utility:&#x000A;&#x000A;   SCORE                   -- check your current score (max: 20)&#x000A;&#x000A;   INVENTORY  /  I         -- check what you are carrying&#x000A;&#x000A;   AGAIN  /  G             -- repeat the last command&#x000A;&#x000A;   QUIT                    -- end the game&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;============================================================&#x000A;&#x000A;                     YOUR OBJECTIVE                          &#x000A;&#x000A;============================================================&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Explore the forest. Find your ally Xilar, trapped in the Ravine&#x000A;&#x000A;to the east, and free him. Then reach the Ghanrion Camp to warn&#x000A;&#x000A;your people. When the moment comes, choose how your people will face&#x000A;&#x000A;the humans who have crashed on your world.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Your choices will determine the ending.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;TIP: Start by talking to the character beside you. Type TALK TO ZARB.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;The forest glows softly around you. Zarb stands nearby, watching&#x000A;&#x000A;the eastern sky with restless, flickering eyes.&#x000A;&#x000A;Before Andromeda: The Sky Breaks&#x000A;Episode 1 - The Sky Breaks by Saturnio Games&#x000A;Release 1 / Serial number 260526 / Inform 7 v10.1.2 / D&#x000A;&#x000A;Bioluminescent Forest&#x000A;A vast forest where every plant pulses with soft blue and green light. Bioluminescent spores drift like slow snow between towering trees, and the air hums with quiet, ancient life.&#x000A;&#x000A;A massive fallen tree blocks the northern path to the Ghanrion Camp. To the EAST the ground drops away toward the Ravine, and to the WEST a rocky path climbs toward the Observation Rock.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Zarb here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
