  <item nodeId="node-307">
    <command xml:space="preserve">talk to Zarb</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Zarb communicates through a series of soft bioluminescent pulses and deliberate gestures. Somehow, you understand every word.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Something fell from the sky -- to the west. It burns, and it brought soldiers with it. They will push deeper into the forest. We must warn the camp, but the elder will not act on my word alone. Xilar carries the elder's trust."&#x000A;&#x000A;He pauses, his skin flickering with anxious light.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Xilar was scouting the Ravine when the debris came down on him. Please -- free him first. Go EAST to find him. Type HELP XILAR when you reach him."&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-308"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-308">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ravine&#x000A;A deep, rocky ravine. The walls are jagged and the air is cold and damp. Somewhere beneath the fallen debris you can hear faint, pained breathing.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the WEST the glow of the forest beckons. Below you, darkness hints at underground tunnels -- go DOWN to explore them.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Xilar here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-309"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-309">
    <command xml:space="preserve">talk to xilar</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Xilar winces in pain but holds your gaze with clear, determined eyes.&#x000A;&#x000A;"The debris... I cannot shift it alone. Free me, and I will lead you past the fallen tree to the camp. The elder must be warned before the humans reach the treeline."&#x000A;&#x000A;He glances at the rubble pressing down on him.&#x000A;&#x000A;Type HELP XILAR to attempt to free him.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-310"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-310">
    <command xml:space="preserve">help xilar</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You brace yourself and drag the heavy debris aside piece by piece. It takes every ounce of your strength.&#x000A;&#x000A;Xilar pulls himself free with a sharp exhale, checks his injuries with practised calm, and rises to his feet.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Thank you," he says simply. "The camp -- now. Follow me back WEST. I know a way around the fallen tree."&#x000A;&#x000A;The northern path to the Ghanrion Camp is now accessible -- return WEST to the forest, and then go NORTH.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Your score has just gone up by five points.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-311"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-311">
    <command xml:space="preserve">w</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Bioluminescent Forest&#x000A;A vast forest where every plant pulses with soft blue and green light. Bioluminescent spores drift like slow snow between towering trees, and the air hums with quiet, ancient life.&#x000A;&#x000A;A massive fallen tree blocks the northern path to the Ghanrion Camp. To the EAST the ground drops away toward the Ravine, and to the WEST a rocky path climbs toward the Observation Rock.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Xilar and Zarb here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-312"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-312">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ravine&#x000A;A deep, rocky ravine. The walls are jagged and the air is cold and damp. Somewhere beneath the fallen debris you can hear faint, pained breathing.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the WEST the glow of the forest beckons. Below you, darkness hints at underground tunnels -- go DOWN to explore them.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-313"/>
    </children>
  </item>
