  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-338">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;A living settlement woven among ancient trees. Bioluminescent lanterns sway between branches, casting the settlement in warm, shifting light. The elder Vael moves with quiet authority between the shelters.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the SOUTH lies the Bioluminescent Forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Vael here.&#x000A;&#x000A;The moment you arrive at the camp, the ground shakes with the deep percussion of approaching footsteps.&#x000A;&#x000A;Human soldiers emerge from the southern treeline, weapons raised, visors reflecting the bioluminescent light. The entire camp falls utterly silent.&#x000A;&#x000A;Vael steps forward alone. His arms are wide, his palms open. His voice is very low.&#x000A;&#x000A;"They are afraid. And fear, more than hatred, makes them dangerous."&#x000A;&#x000A;He turns to you.&#x000A;&#x000A;"What will you do?"&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;You have three choices:&#x000A;&#x000A;  HELP VAEL -- Step forward and stand beside the elder.&#x000A;&#x000A;  GUIDE YOUNG -- Lead the children and elders through the underground tunnels to safety.&#x000A;&#x000A;  OBSERVE -- Pull back into the shadows and bear witness.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Your score has just gone up by five points.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-339"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-339">
    <command xml:space="preserve">observe</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You step back into the deep shadow of the trees and become very still.&#x000A;&#x000A;Vael speaks to the soldiers in slow, measured tones. They cannot understand his words, but his absolute calm is a language of its own -- one that transcends species and training and fear.&#x000A;&#x000A;The standoff holds. Neither side advances. Neither side fires.&#x000A;&#x000A;Hours pass. Eventually the soldiers withdraw toward the crash site. Vael watches them go, unmoving, until the last footstep fades.&#x000A;&#x000A;He does not look for you. But as he finally turns back toward the camp, you have the quiet sense that he always knew you were there.&#x000A;&#x000A;You wonder, in the long silence that follows, what your presence beside him might have changed.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** The Silent Witness -- You watched, but did not act. Some choices are made by not choosing. The forest will remember. ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;In that game you scored 37 out of a possible 20, in 29 turns.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-340">
    <command xml:space="preserve">talk to zarb</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Zarb communicates through a series of soft bioluminescent pulses and deliberate gestures. Somehow, you understand every word.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Something fell from the sky -- to the west. It burns, and it brought soldiers with it. They will push deeper into the forest. We must warn the camp, but the elder will not act on my word alone. Xilar carries the elder's trust."&#x000A;&#x000A;He pauses, his skin flickering with anxious light.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Xilar was scouting the Ravine when the debris came down on him. Please -- free him first. Go EAST to find him. Type HELP XILAR when you reach him."&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-341"/>
    </children>
  </item>
