  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-345">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;A living settlement woven among ancient trees. Bioluminescent lanterns sway between branches, casting the settlement in warm, shifting light. The elder Vael moves with quiet authority between the shelters.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the SOUTH lies the Bioluminescent Forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Vael here.&#x000A;&#x000A;The moment you arrive at the camp, the ground shakes with the deep percussion of approaching footsteps.&#x000A;&#x000A;Human soldiers emerge from the southern treeline, weapons raised, visors reflecting the bioluminescent light. The entire camp falls utterly silent.&#x000A;&#x000A;Vael steps forward alone. His arms are wide, his palms open. His voice is very low.&#x000A;&#x000A;"They are afraid. And fear, more than hatred, makes them dangerous."&#x000A;&#x000A;He turns to you.&#x000A;&#x000A;"What will you do?"&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;You have three choices:&#x000A;&#x000A;  HELP VAEL -- Step forward and stand beside the elder.&#x000A;&#x000A;  GUIDE YOUNG -- Lead the children and elders through the underground tunnels to safety.&#x000A;&#x000A;  OBSERVE -- Pull back into the shadows and bear witness.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Your score has just gone up by five points.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-346"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-346">
    <command xml:space="preserve">help vael</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You walk forward and stand beside Vael.&#x000A;&#x000A;The soldiers freeze.&#x000A;&#x000A;Something about the image -- the ancient elder and a being they cannot categorise, standing together without weapons, without aggression, without fear -- fractures their certainty. Training accounts for hostility. It does not account for this.&#x000A;&#x000A;A long silence stretches across the camp. The wind moves through the luminescent leaves.&#x000A;&#x000A;Slowly, one soldier lowers his weapon. Then another. Then all of them.&#x000A;&#x000A;Vael places a hand on your shoulder and says nothing. He does not need to.&#x000A;&#x000A;Behind you, the camp exhales.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** A Fragile Peace -- You stood with the Ghanrion and turned fear into stillness. The first step toward understanding has been taken. ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;In that game you scored 15 out of a possible 20, in 6 turns.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-347"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-347">
    <command xml:space="preserve">undo </command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;[Previous turn undone.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-348"/>
    </children>
