  <item nodeId="node-373">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Bioluminescent Forest&#x000A;A vast forest where every plant pulses with soft blue and green light. Bioluminescent spores drift like slow snow between towering trees, and the air hums with quiet, ancient life.&#x000A;&#x000A;A massive fallen tree blocks the northern path to the Ghanrion Camp. To the EAST the ground drops away toward the Ravine, and to the WEST a rocky path climbs toward the Observation Rock.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Xilar and Zarb here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-374"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-374">
    <command xml:space="preserve">talk to xilar</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Xilar nods with quiet, steady gratitude.&#x000A;&#x000A;"I owe you a debt I will not forget. These forests hold no secrets from me. The fallen tree across the north path is no obstacle -- I know every hidden trail. Walk with me and I will guide you safely to the camp."&#x000A;&#x000A;He glances north. "You can go NORTH now from the forest."&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-375"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-375">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;A living settlement woven among ancient trees. Bioluminescent lanterns sway between branches, casting the settlement in warm, shifting light. The elder Vael moves with quiet authority between the shelters.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the SOUTH lies the Bioluminescent Forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Vael here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-376"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-376">
    <command xml:space="preserve">talk to vael</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Vael's expression is grave but utterly composed.&#x000A;&#x000A;"There is no more time for words. The soldiers are here. You must decide what kind of person you are."&#x000A;&#x000A;He meets your eyes steadily.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your three choices are:&#x000A;&#x000A;  HELP VAEL -- Stand beside the elder and face the soldiers together.&#x000A;&#x000A;  GUIDE YOUNG -- Lead the children and elders through the hidden tunnels to safety.&#x000A;&#x000A;  OBSERVE -- Pull back into the shadows and bear witness.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-377"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-377">
    <command xml:space="preserve">guide young </command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You move quickly and without a word, gathering the young Ghanrion with calm, urgent gestures. Through the tunnels beneath the Ravine -- tunnels you now know well -- you lead them in single file through the glowing dark.&#x000A;&#x000A;Behind you, voices rise. Tense and confused. But no pursuit comes.&#x000A;&#x000A;The children emerge into the far forest, blinking in the cold air. One of the youngest looks back at you, her luminescent eyes wide and full of something that might be gratitude, or wonder, or both.&#x000A;&#x000A;Above ground, the standoff continues. You have saved some. The rest remains unwritten.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** Partial Escape -- The young were saved. The fate of the camp is still unwritten. Perhaps that is enough for now. ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;In that game you scored 16 out of a possible 20, in 23 turns.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-378"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-378">
    <command xml:space="preserve">undo </command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;[Previous turn undone.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-379"/>
    </children>
  </item>
