  <item nodeId="node-382">
    <command xml:space="preserve">s</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Bioluminescent Forest&#x000A;A vast forest where every plant pulses with soft blue and green light. Bioluminescent spores drift like slow snow between towering trees, and the air hums with quiet, ancient life.&#x000A;&#x000A;A massive fallen tree blocks the northern path to the Ghanrion Camp. To the EAST the ground drops away toward the Ravine, and to the WEST a rocky path climbs toward the Observation Rock.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Xilar and Zarb here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-383"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-383">
    <command xml:space="preserve">talk to zarb</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Zarb communicates through a series of soft bioluminescent pulses and deliberate gestures. Somehow, you understand every word.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Something fell from the sky -- to the west. It burns, and it brought soldiers with it. They will push deeper into the forest. We must warn the camp, but the elder will not act on my word alone. Xilar carries the elder's trust."&#x000A;&#x000A;He pauses, his skin flickering with anxious light.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Xilar was scouting the Ravine when the debris came down on him. Please -- free him first. Go EAST to find him. Type HELP XILAR when you reach him."&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-384"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-384">
    <command xml:space="preserve">use telephaty</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">I didn't understand that sentence.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-385"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-385">
    <command xml:space="preserve">USE TELEPATHY</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You close your eyes and push a weak telepathic signal outward through the forest network.&#x000A;&#x000A;For a moment, nothing. Then a tremor moves through the bioluminescent light all around you -- the plants respond like a living relay, carrying your signal through root and spore and branch.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Zarb spins toward you, eyes wide.&#x000A;&#x000A;"You... you sent that?" His skin flashes bright white with shock.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;The forest hums softly in reply.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Your score has just gone up by two points.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-386"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-386">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ravine&#x000A;A deep, rocky ravine. The walls are jagged and the air is cold and damp. Somewhere beneath the fallen debris you can hear faint, pained breathing.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the WEST the glow of the forest beckons. Below you, darkness hints at underground tunnels -- go DOWN to explore them.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-387"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-387">
    <command xml:space="preserve">w</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Bioluminescent Forest&#x000A;A vast forest where every plant pulses with soft blue and green light. Bioluminescent spores drift like slow snow between towering trees, and the air hums with quiet, ancient life.&#x000A;&#x000A;A massive fallen tree blocks the northern path to the Ghanrion Camp. To the EAST the ground drops away toward the Ravine, and to the WEST a rocky path climbs toward the Observation Rock.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Xilar and Zarb here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-388"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-388">
    <command xml:space="preserve">help xilar</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Xilar is already free. He is ready to guide you north.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-389"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-389">
    <command xml:space="preserve">n</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;A living settlement woven among ancient trees. Bioluminescent lanterns sway between branches, casting the settlement in warm, shifting light. The elder Vael moves with quiet authority between the shelters.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the SOUTH lies the Bioluminescent Forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Vael here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-390"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-390">
    <command xml:space="preserve">help vael</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You walk forward and stand beside Vael.&#x000A;&#x000A;The soldiers freeze.&#x000A;&#x000A;Something about the image -- the ancient elder and a being they cannot categorise, standing together without weapons, without aggression, without fear -- fractures their certainty. Training accounts for hostility. It does not account for this.&#x000A;&#x000A;A long silence stretches across the camp. The wind moves through the luminescent leaves.&#x000A;&#x000A;Slowly, one soldier lowers his weapon. Then another. Then all of them.&#x000A;&#x000A;Vael places a hand on your shoulder and says nothing. He does not need to.&#x000A;&#x000A;Behind you, the camp exhales.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** A Fragile Peace -- You stood with the Ghanrion and turned fear into stillness. The first step toward understanding has been taken. ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;In that game you scored 20 out of a possible 20, in 33 turns.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-391"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-391">
    <command xml:space="preserve">undo</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Ghanrion Camp&#x000A;[Previous turn undone.]&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-392"/>
    </children>
  </item>
